Ok, the question here is this.  I have 3 statements in the transform

{
  "title" : "casey is stellar"
}

{ 
  "transformation" : "STELLAR"
 ,"output" : [ "better_title", "title"]
 ,"config" : {
          "better_title" : "title"
         ,"title" : "SOME_UDF_THAT_CAN_RET_NULL()"
         ,"title" : "if title == null then GET_RANDOM_TITLE()
                    }
}

If the second function results in the removal of title... what do we do?  What was the intent of that null ( from a UDF maybe ), we don't know if it was to remove or not.

Currently you cannot have two statements in stellar field transformations with the same variable, so 
```
{
"transformation" : "STELLAR"
,"output" : [ "better_title", "title"]
,"config" : {
"better_title" : "title"
,"title" : "SOME_UDF_THAT_CAN_RET_NULL()"
,"title" : "if title == null then GET_RANDOM_TITLE()
}
}
```
would evaluate only the last `title` expression.  It's a problem with our use of maps and why in enrichment we transitioned to lists of strings as an alternative ðŸ˜¢
